From: Pablo Neira Ayuso <pablo@netfilter.org>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 13:48:48 +0100
Subject: netfilter: xt_CT: drop pending enqueued packets on template removal
Git-commit: f62a218a946b19bb59abdd5361da85fa4606b96b
Patch-mainline: v6.18 or v6.18-rc8 (next release)
References: CVE-2026-23391 bsc#1260566

Templates refer to objects that can go away while packets are sitting in
nfqueue refer to:

- helper, this can be an issue on module removal.
- timeout policy, nfnetlink_cttimeout might remove it.

The use of templates with zone and event cache filter are safe, since
this just copies values.

Flush these enqueued packets in case the template rule gets removed.

Fixes: 24de58f46516 ("netfilter: xt_CT: allow to attach timeout policy + glue code")
Reported-by: Yiming Qian <yimingqian591@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Pablo Neira Ayuso <pablo@netfilter.org>
Signed-off-by: Florian Westphal <fw@strlen.de>
Acked-by: Fernando Fernandez Mancera <fmancera@suse.de>
---
 net/netfilter/nf_queue.c |    1 +
 net/netfilter/xt_CT.c    |    4 ++++
 2 files changed, 5 insertions(+)

--- a/net/netfilter/nf_queue.c
+++ b/net/netfilter/nf_queue.c
@@ -111,6 +111,7 @@ unsigned int nf_queue_nf_hook_drop(struc
 
 	return count;
 }
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(nf_queue_nf_hook_drop);
 
 static int __nf_queue(struct sk_buff *skb, const struct nf_hook_state *state,
 		      struct nf_hook_entry *hook_entry, unsigned int queuenum)
--- a/net/netfilter/xt_CT.c
+++ b/net/netfilter/xt_CT.c
@@ -19,6 +19,7 @@
 #include <net/netfilter/nf_conntrack_ecache.h>
 #include <net/netfilter/nf_conntrack_timeout.h>
 #include <net/netfilter/nf_conntrack_zones.h>
+#include "nf_internals.h"
 
 static inline int xt_ct_target(struct sk_buff *skb, struct nf_conn *ct)
 {
@@ -344,6 +345,9 @@ static void xt_ct_tg_destroy(const struc
 	struct nf_conn_help *help;
 
 	if (ct) {
+		if (info->helper[0] || info->timeout[0])
+			nf_queue_nf_hook_drop(par->net);
+
 		help = nfct_help(ct);
 		if (help)
 			nf_conntrack_helper_put(help->helper);
